@TITLE "fuse-utils(1)ĀmanualĀpage"
 @{" " link "'#toc'/MAIN"}Table of Contents

 @{" " link "'#toc0'/MAIN"}Name fuse-utils - various ZX Spectrum related utilities @{" " link "'#toc1'/MAIN"}Description The Fuse (Free Unix Spectrum Emulator) utilities are a small suite of utilities relating to some of the file formats used by ZX Spectrum emulators. The currently available utilities are: 

@{"i"}createhdf@{"ui"} Create a blank IDE hard disk image in .hdf format. 

@{"i"}listbasic@{"ui"} Extract the BASIC program from a ZX Spectrum file. 

@{"i"}raw2hdf@{"ui"} Create an .hdf hard disk image from a raw data file. 

@{"i"}rzxcheck@{"ui"} Verify the competition mode signature in an RZX input recording file. 

@{"i"}rzxdump@{"ui"} Display the contents of an RZX file. 

@{"i"}rzxtool@{"ui"} Make simple modifications to an RZX file. 

@{"i"}scl2trd@{"ui"} Convert .scl disk images into .trd format. 

@{"i"}snap2tzx@{"ui"} Convert a snapshot into a .tzx tape image. 

@{"i"}snapconv@{"ui"} Convert between various snapshot formats. 

@{"i"}tapeconv@{"ui"} Convert between various tape formats. 

@{"i"}tzxlist@{"ui"} Display the contents of a .tzx tape image. @{" " link "'#toc2'/MAIN"}See Also @{" " link "'createhdf.1'/MAIN"}@{"i"}createhdf@{"ui"}(1) , @{" " link "'fuse.1'/MAIN"}@{"i"}fuse@{"ui"}(1) , @{" " link "'libspectrum.3'/MAIN"}@{"i"}libspectrum@{"ui"}(3) , @{" " link "'listbasic.1'/MAIN"}@{"i"}listbasic@{"ui"}(1) , @{" " link "'raw2hdf.1'/MAIN"}@{"i"}raw2hdf@{"ui"}(1) , @{" " link "'rzxcheck.1'/MAIN"}@{"i"}rzxcheck@{"ui"}(1) , @{" " link "'rzxdump.1'/MAIN"}@{"i"}rzxdump@{"ui"}(1) , @{" " link "'rzxtool.1'/MAIN"}@{"i"}rzxtool@{"ui"}(1) , @{" " link "'scl2trd.1'/MAIN"}@{"i"}scl2trd@{"ui"}(1) , @{" " link "'snap2tzx.1'/MAIN"}@{"i"}snap2tzx@{"ui"}(1) , @{" " link "'snapconv.1'/MAIN"}@{"i"}snapconv@{"ui"}(1) , @{" " link "'tapeconv.1'/MAIN"}@{"i"}tapeconv@{"ui"}(1) , @{" " link "'tzxlist.1'/MAIN"}@{"i"}tzxlist@{"ui"}(1) , @{" " link "'xspect.1'/MAIN"}@{"i"}xspect@{"ui"}(1) , @{" " link "'xzx.1'/MAIN"}@{"i"}xzx@{"ui"}(1) 

The comp.sys.sinclair Spectrum FAQ, at 
@{" " link "'http://www.worldofspectrum.org/faq/index.html.guide/MAIN"}@{"i"}http://www.worldofspectrum.org/faq/index.html@{"ui"}. @{" " link "'#toc3'/MAIN"}Author Philip Kendall (philip-fuse@shadowmagic.org.uk) and others; see the individual man pages for more details. 


